<p>Okay so now that weâ€™ve created a Github account, we need something else for our computer to communicate with Github, and thatâ€™s where <a href="https://git-scm.com/">Git</a> comes into play. Now technically speaking, git is already installed on your computer but (hopefully) youâ€™ll see why I like this slightly more. Go ahead and install <a href="https://git-scm.com/">Git</a> onto your computer. After you go through the installation and all, you should have â€˜Git Bashâ€™ when you search for it; open it.</p>

