<p>Now, the beautiful thing about installing from <a href="https://git-scm.com/">Git</a> is that it also installs something called <a href="http://mingw.org/">â€œMinGWâ€</a>. This will essentially give you a â€˜Unixâ€™ feeling, as in most of the basic commands you type in here will also apply to Linux and Mac. Now letâ€™s start syncing Github with your computer! Type in the following commands. <strong>NOTE:</strong> if you donâ€™t want to set up SSH with your Github account, you can skip all the instructions regarding SSH. You will instead clone your repository using HTTPS.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git config <span class="nt">--global</span> user.name <span class="s2">"H Son"</span>       <span class="c"># replace "H Son" with your name</span>
